    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I use Windows too, and I confirm this is not a geth problem. With the Windows console - like with many other shell and programming languages - you use \\\" as the escape character when you want actually insert a _double quote character_ inside a string, and the string itself is delimited by double quotes.\n\nSo writing `--datadir=\"H:\\Blockchain\\\"` you are actually passing `H:\\Blockchain\"` as parameter. You can avoid that behavior removing both double quote:\n\n`F:\\geth>geth.exe --datadir H:\\blockchain\\`\n\nNote that you can do this because in your case there are no spaces in the datadir path.\n",
